


to see the services that this user has access to:

aws ls



------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------




sync a folder in our system to a folder in aws storage:


aws s3 sync myfolder/ s3://my-directory




------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------




install docker on a amazon EC2 instance:



sudo amazon-linux-extras install docker



sudo service docker start




------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------




ECS = Amazon Elastic Container Service   ---->    for running containers




------------------------------------------------------




temporarily access to private objects: (seconds)

aws s3 presign s3://my-bucket/my-pic --expires-in 300

aws s3 presign s3://my-bucket/my-directory --expires-in 300



------------------------------------------------------




list of all s3 storages:

aws s3 ls




------------------------------------------------------




aws s3 ls my-bucket



aws s3 ls s3://my-bucket/my-directory/



------------------------------------------------------





copy a file  to/from  aws storage:


aws cp ~/Desktop/myfile.txt s3://my-directory-in-aws-storage/myfile.txt







aws cp s3://my-directory-in-aws-storage/myfile.txt ~/Desktop/myfile.txt 





